    caption: [Coupling of electron transfer and ATP synthesis in mito- chondria. In experiments to demonstrate coupling, mitochondria are sus- pended in a buffered medium and an O2 electrode monitors O2 consump- tion. At intervals, samples are removed and assayed for the presence of ATP. (a) Addition of ADP and Pi alone results in little or no increase in either respiration (O2 consumption; black) or ATP synthesis (red). When succinate is added, respiration begins immediately and ATP is synthe-],
