  "19-21": (
    caption: [Two chemical uncouplers of oxidative phosphorylation. Both DNP and FCCP have a dissociable proton and are very hydrophobic. They carry protons across the inner mitochondrial membrane, dissipat- ing the proton gradient. Both also uncouple photophosphorylation (see Fig. 19–65). (Fig. 19–22). Mitochondria manipulated so as to impose a difference of proton concentration and a separation of charge across the inner membrane syn- thesize ATP in the absence of an oxidizable sub- strate; the proton-motive force alone suffices to drive ATP synthesis. c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 750 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 750 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 750 (a)],
