  "19-33": (
    caption: [Structure of bovine F1-ATPase in a complex with its regula- tory protein IF1. (Derived from PDB ID 1OHH) Two F1 molecules are viewed here as in Figure 19–25c. The inhibitor IF1 (red) binds to the (cid:2)(cid:3) interface of the subunits in the diphosphate (ADP) conformation ((cid:2)-ADP and (cid:3)-ADP), freezing the two F1 complexes and thereby blocking ATP hydrolysis (and synthesis). (Parts of IF1 that failed to resolve in the crystals of F1 are shown in light red as they occur in crystals of isolated IF1.) This complex is stable only at the low cytosolic pH characteristic of cells that are producing ATP by glycolysis; when aerobic metabolism resumes, the cytosolic pH rises, the inhibitor is destabilized, and ATP synthase becomes active. c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 761 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 761 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 19.3 Regulation of Oxidative Phosphorylation 761],
