  "19-39": (
    caption: [Role of cytochrome c in apoptosis. Cytochrome c is a small, soluble, mitochondrial protein, located in the intermembrane space, that carries electrons between Complex III and Complex IV during respi- ration. In a completely separate role, as outlined here, it acts as a trigger for apoptosis by stimulating the activation of a family of proteases called caspases.],
