  "19-42": (
    caption: [Single cells contain many mitochondria. A typical animal cell has hundreds or thousands of mitochondria, some fraction of which may contain genomes with mutations that affect mitochondrial function. This ovine (sheep) kidney epithelial cell was cultured in the laboratory, fixed, and then stained with fluorescent probes that show mitochondria as gold, microfilaments of actin as red, and nuclei as green when observed in the fluorescence microscope. c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 767 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 c19OxidativePhosphorylationAndPhotophosphorylation.indd Page 767 27/09/12 1:34 PM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 19.5 Mitochondrial Genes: Their Origin and the Effects of Mutations 767],
