  "19-44": (
    caption: [Defective oxidative phosphorylation in pancreatic (cid:3) cells blocks insulin secretion. In the normal situation depicted here, when blood glucose rises, the production of ATP in (cid:3) cells increases. ATP, by blocking K(cid:2) channels, depolarizes the plasma membrane and thus opens the voltage-gated Ca2(cid:2) channels. The resulting influx of Ca2(cid:2) triggers exo- cytosis of insulin-containing secretory vesicles, releasing insulin. When oxidative phosphorylation in (cid:3) cells is defective, \[ATP\] is never sufficient to trigger this process, and insulin is not released.],
