    caption: [Functional modules of photosynthetic machinery in purple bacteria and green sulfur bacteria. (a) In purple bacteria, light energy drives electrons from the reaction-center P870 through pheophy- tin (Pheo), a quinone (Q), and the cytochrome bc1 complex, then through cytochrome c2 and thus back to the reaction center. Electron flow through the cytochrome bc1 complex causes proton pumping, creating an electro-],
