  "19-58": (
    caption: [Integration of photosystems I and II in chloroplasts. This “Z scheme” shows the pathway of electron transfer from H2O (lower left) to NADP(cid:2) (far right) in noncyclic photosynthesis. The position on the ver- tical scale of each electron carrier reflects its standard reduction potential. To raise the energy of electrons derived from H2O to the energy level re- quired to reduce NADP(cid:2) to NADPH, each electron must be “lifted” twice (heavy arrows) by photons absorbed in PSII and PSI. One photon is re- quired per electron in each photosystem. After excitation, the high-energy],
