  "19-65": (
    caption: [Proton and electron circuits during photophosphorylation. Electrons (blue arrows) move from H2O through PSII, through the inter- mediate chain of carriers, through PSI, and finally to NADP(cid:2). Protons (red arrows) are pumped into the thylakoid lumen by the flow of electrons through the carriers linking PSII and PSI, and reenter the stroma through proton channels formed by the Fo (designated CFo) of ATP synthase. The F1 subunit (CF1) catalyzes synthesis of ATP.],
